Global Funds Sell Net 6.04 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-07-29T03:30:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/global-funds-sell-net-6-04-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors sold a net 6.04
billion rupees ($137 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, declined 26.6 percent to 714.2 billion rupees, or
38.4 percent of the gross market position on the last day of
contracts for July, according to the exchangeâ€™s website. Open
interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 647 million rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
